President Obama announced the White House Tribal Nations Conference, which will take place on November 5th, 2009. The conference aims to provide leaders from the 564 federally recognized tribes the opportunity to interact directly with the President and representatives from his Administration. Each tribe will be invited to send one representative to the conference. President Obama expressed his interest in hearing from leaders in Indian Country about how his Administration can meet their needs and improve their lives. The conference is part of the ongoing consultation process and aims to strengthen the Nation-to-Nation relationship. Media credentialing information will be released at a later date.